WEBVTT

00:03.103 --> 00:04.636
Look what someone
left in our mailbox... again.

00:04.638 --> 00:06.171
Wait, that's like
our fifth one, isn't it?

00:06.173 --> 00:07.606
It's getting
kind of creepy.

00:07.608 --> 00:09.475
Oh, relax... it's probably
just from victor,

00:09.477 --> 00:11.010
That flower-delivery guy
I dated.

00:11.012 --> 00:12.678
Who's victor?
We never heard about him.

00:12.680 --> 00:15.481
Oh, because I knew you'd never
let me go out with an ex-con.

00:15.483 --> 00:17.149
Hey, maybe it's dylan
trying to win you back.

00:17.151 --> 00:18.350
Mm.

00:18.352 --> 00:20.352
So, victor...
It's a closed door?

00:20.354 --> 00:22.187
Maybe it's not a guy
who's in love with Haley.

00:22.189 --> 00:23.622
Oh, thank you.

00:23.624 --> 00:25.457
Maybe it's a guy
who's obsessed with Haley

00:25.459 --> 00:26.792
And is getting plastic surgery
to look like her

00:26.794 --> 00:28.127
So he can replace her
and live her life.

00:28.129 --> 00:29.328
Luke.

00:29.330 --> 00:31.030
So they can <i>only</i>
be for Haley?

00:31.032 --> 00:33.232
Of course not. Haley isn't
the only hottie living here.

00:33.234 --> 00:36.335
I washed the car in
my cheer shorts the other day.

00:36.337 --> 00:38.037
I definitely
felt eyes on me.

00:38.039 --> 00:41.040
Has it ever occurred to you that
those flowers could be for me?

00:41.042 --> 00:44.043
What do you mean?
I mean, like,
from my boyfriend.

00:44.045 --> 00:45.544
What?
You have a boyfriend?

00:45.546 --> 00:47.579
And you thought
<i>my</i> thing was crazy.

00:48.983 --> 00:52.084
Captions by <b> <i>vitac</i> </b>...

01:00.326 --> 01:01.427
¶¶¶

01:01.429 --> 01:02.828
Alex,
you have a boyfriend?

01:02.830 --> 01:04.830
You can't just drop that
and leave.

01:04.831 --> 01:07.166
Honey, it is so exciting.
Why didn't you tell us?

01:07.168 --> 01:08.600
Because I knew
you'd get all weird

01:08.602 --> 01:10.102
And ask
a million stupid questions.

01:10.104 --> 01:11.703
What does he look like?
How did you meet him?

01:11.705 --> 01:15.340
Okay, I'll show you a photo.

01:15.342 --> 01:18.210
Well, I would,
but now my phone's not working.

01:18.212 --> 01:19.511
Hmm.
Hmm.

01:19.513 --> 01:21.513
Oh! Oh, here he is.

01:21.515 --> 01:23.082
In the supermarket
flyer?

01:23.084 --> 01:24.583
That's him
pondering the pork chops?

01:24.585 --> 01:26.552
What's to ponder?
They're $4.59 a pound.

01:26.554 --> 01:28.454
I don't understand.
Why is he in this?

01:28.456 --> 01:29.888
He's a model, mom.

01:29.890 --> 01:31.523
Oh, wait, wait.
Your boyfriend's a model?

01:31.525 --> 01:33.192
Well,
how did you meet him?

01:33.194 --> 01:34.760
There's not much crossover

01:34.762 --> 01:37.463
For a national honor society
student and a pork model.

01:37.465 --> 01:39.064
Well, actually,
it's a really long story.

01:39.066 --> 01:40.466
I...

01:40.468 --> 01:42.601
Oh, well...
it's him.

01:42.603 --> 01:44.069
Hey, hold on.

01:44.071 --> 01:45.938
This is terrific news.

01:45.940 --> 01:48.207
I can't believe
she didn't tell us about him.

01:48.209 --> 01:49.875
Oh, <i>that's</i>
what you can't believe?

01:49.877 --> 01:52.044
What do you mean?
Phil, it is a little weird.

01:52.046 --> 01:53.612
I mean, suddenly
she has this boyfriend.

01:53.614 --> 01:55.647
She wants to show us a picture
on her phone, but she can't,

01:55.649 --> 01:57.816
And magically
he's in today's paper?

01:59.220 --> 02:01.453
I don't even want to say it.
Haley.

02:01.455 --> 02:02.754
She's making it up.
Mm.

02:02.756 --> 02:03.989
Why would she do that?

02:03.991 --> 02:05.557
Maybe she's upset

02:05.559 --> 02:07.593
That none of us thought
those roses could be for her.

02:07.595 --> 02:09.394
Oh, and remember when
she couldn't get a
date for homecoming?

02:09.395 --> 02:11.263
She said she didn't care,
but I caught her crying
in her room.

02:11.265 --> 02:13.599
Mm-hmm. Oh, honey,
what did you say to her?

02:13.601 --> 02:15.734
Oh, I-I was super late,
so I didn't really...

02:15.736 --> 02:16.768
This is sad.

02:16.770 --> 02:18.303
Alex has great news

02:18.305 --> 02:19.638
And her own mother and sister
don't believe her?

02:19.640 --> 02:21.507
I want to.
Well, I <i>do</i> believe her.

02:21.509 --> 02:23.609
I'm gonna tell her to invite
this boyfriend over for dinner,

02:23.611 --> 02:25.644
And I'll be serving a big,
old platter of "I told you so."

02:25.646 --> 02:27.346
Oh, great.

02:27.348 --> 02:29.581
Maybe you could also serve
unicorn burgers and magic beans,

02:29.583 --> 02:31.517
And I'll invite my boyfriend,
bigfoot!

02:31.519 --> 02:35.120
Still better than dylan.

02:35.122 --> 02:38.357
Okay. I got
a surprise for you.

02:38.359 --> 02:39.992
It better
not be another baby.

02:39.994 --> 02:42.327
Ta-da!

02:42.329 --> 02:44.196
Is there something fun
behind the couch?

02:44.198 --> 02:47.833
An edgar vanderkoff hand-crafted
blanc de blanc sofa.

02:47.835 --> 02:49.768
It was a wedding gift
to ourselves.

02:49.770 --> 02:51.303
Plus,
we're showing Lily

02:51.305 --> 02:53.305
That we trust her enough
to let us have one nice thing.

02:53.307 --> 02:54.806
When you think about it
like that,

02:54.808 --> 02:56.608
It's really a gift
for Lily.
Yeah.

02:56.610 --> 02:58.644
Ohh! Okay, whoa.

02:58.646 --> 03:00.779
We only get on this couch
when we know we're not dirty.

03:00.781 --> 03:02.681
That's why
we got <i>her</i> the couch.

03:02.683 --> 03:04.550
To teach her
about respect.

03:04.552 --> 03:06.351
Legs a little wider
please.

03:06.353 --> 03:08.320
Is that a cookie
in your back pocket?

03:08.322 --> 03:09.655
Yep.
Okay.

03:09.657 --> 03:12.391
Bup-up-up!
Hey, nice and slow.

03:13.893 --> 03:15.360
Unh-unh-unh-unh,
watching that.

03:15.362 --> 03:18.897
But now that I got you here,
what do you think?

03:18.899 --> 03:22.067
That you wore cargo shorts
to my middle-school graduation,

03:22.069 --> 03:24.636
But you're putting on a bow tie
for some dog's birthday party.

03:24.638 --> 03:27.039
It's all good fun.
The birnbaums can't have kids.

03:27.041 --> 03:28.574
They like to do it up big
for buster.

03:28.576 --> 03:30.242
I had my fifth birthday
in a break room

03:30.244 --> 03:32.477
Of a der wienerschnitzel,
but good for buster.

03:32.479 --> 03:33.912
Why are you so cranky?

03:35.382 --> 03:38.584
This kid at school
ripped me off for 40 bucks

03:38.586 --> 03:39.818
In a pyramid scheme.

03:39.820 --> 03:41.320
Did this
have something to do

03:41.322 --> 03:43.222
With that broken plastic pyramid
on your dresser?

03:43.224 --> 03:44.990
It looked like marble
in the picture.

03:44.992 --> 03:46.258
Oh, man.

03:46.260 --> 03:47.426
Where were you
when I was growing up?

03:47.428 --> 03:48.660
I'd have had
your dice and cigarettes

03:48.662 --> 03:50.162
Before
you got to homeroom.

03:50.164 --> 03:51.897
Where'd you go to school...
"guys and dolls"?

03:51.899 --> 03:53.565
Bright as you are,
you got to smarten up.

03:53.567 --> 03:56.168
You got to be more suspicious
of people.

03:56.170 --> 03:57.703
Stop being such a patsy.

03:57.705 --> 03:59.571
How is this
for the party?

03:59.573 --> 04:02.241
It's my first time
meeting your dog-park friends.

04:02.243 --> 04:03.742
Fantastic,
but be careful...

04:03.744 --> 04:05.277
Some of these guys are single
in the group.

04:05.279 --> 04:07.079
What a surprise.

04:07.081 --> 04:08.547
Manny,
we won't be late.

04:08.549 --> 04:10.415
I left dinner
for you and Joe,

04:10.417 --> 04:12.684
But don't eat the deviled eggs
that are in the refrigerator

04:12.686 --> 04:14.920
Because they're
for tomorrow's picnic.

04:14.922 --> 04:16.721
What picnic...
Somebody's cat going to college?

04:16.724 --> 04:18.724
No, some of Gloria's friends
are getting their green cards.

04:18.726 --> 04:20.192
It's actually
a nice group.

04:20.194 --> 04:22.361
Yes, they're very decent,
hardworking people.

04:22.363 --> 04:24.863
Jay met them
at mirabelle's fake wedding.

04:24.865 --> 04:26.531
Zooboo!

04:26.533 --> 04:28.533
No, you've already watched
"zooboo" six times today.

04:28.535 --> 04:29.701
We're gonna watch
a classic movie

04:29.703 --> 04:31.036
Right here
on the big screen.

04:31.038 --> 04:32.537
You better let him
watch his show.

04:32.539 --> 04:33.639
If not,
he's gonna freak out.

04:33.641 --> 04:34.973
Yesterday
I turned it off,

04:34.975 --> 04:36.842
And he bit
through one of the pool balls.

04:44.317 --> 04:45.717
Hey, Mitchell.

04:45.719 --> 04:47.319
Hi, uh, um...

04:47.321 --> 04:49.554
B...Renda. Ah!

04:49.556 --> 04:51.223
Yes, you thought I wasn't
gonna remember, didn't you?

04:51.225 --> 04:53.425
So, how's
your first week been?

04:53.427 --> 04:54.426
I'm getting a divorce.

04:54.428 --> 04:56.128
Oh. God.

04:56.130 --> 04:58.463
Um... Well, I did ask, so...

04:58.465 --> 05:00.399
It's really hard to be alone,
you know?

05:00.401 --> 05:02.000
Yeah.

05:02.002 --> 05:04.569
Hey, you know who else
who stays late is, um, stacey.

05:04.571 --> 05:06.338
14 months.
Oh, gosh.

05:06.340 --> 05:08.240
Well, sometimes it's good to get
in and out fast, though, huh?

05:08.242 --> 05:10.242
We haven't had sex
in 14 months.

05:10.244 --> 05:11.977
We were married
20 years.

05:11.979 --> 05:13.512
Well, that's a nice,
round number.

05:13.514 --> 05:15.080
Ohh!
Yeah.

05:15.082 --> 05:17.416
My restless leg syndrome,
like that's a reason to leave?

05:17.418 --> 05:18.984
Gah!
Well, you know,
everybody has...

05:18.986 --> 05:22.120
Especially after
all his habits and requests!

05:22.122 --> 05:25.590
God! I've done more paddling
than lewis and clark!

05:25.592 --> 05:28.026
Hey, stace,
you out there?

05:28.028 --> 05:30.696
Oh, she's gone.
People leave.
Well, you know,

05:30.698 --> 05:33.298
I-if there's anything
that I can do to help you...

05:33.300 --> 05:34.833
Could I stay with you?

05:34.835 --> 05:36.435
What's that?

05:36.437 --> 05:40.005
So, Larry's allowed
to sit on the couch and I'm not?

05:40.007 --> 05:41.540
Well,
Larry is white.

05:41.542 --> 05:43.375
Hey, you chose me.

05:43.377 --> 05:46.178
Oh, uh,
that's not what I meant.

05:47.548 --> 05:49.381
- Hello?
- Hey, Cam.

05:49.383 --> 05:50.782
So, listen, you remember

05:50.784 --> 05:52.517
My... my new friend
at work brenda, right?

05:52.519 --> 05:54.052
Who?

05:54.054 --> 05:55.487
That's right...
the pretty one.
Oh!

05:55.489 --> 05:57.055
Uh, so,
she and her husband

05:57.057 --> 05:58.390
Are... are going
through some problems at home,

05:58.392 --> 05:59.725
And she was wondering

05:59.727 --> 06:01.193
If she might be
able to stay at our house.

06:01.195 --> 06:02.861
Oh, my gosh.
Yes, of course.

06:02.863 --> 06:04.830
Oh,
shoot and darn it!

06:04.832 --> 06:07.032
I thought
we had something.

06:07.034 --> 06:08.467
Mitchell,
I know what you're doing.

06:08.469 --> 06:10.535
Ahh, there's no way
we can reschedule, huh?

06:10.537 --> 06:12.170
Fight your instincts.

06:12.172 --> 06:14.873
This is a chance for you
to show some real compassion.

06:14.875 --> 06:17.242
I need a zoloft.
Okay. Okay.

06:17.244 --> 06:18.877
Well,
I agree with all that,

06:18.879 --> 06:21.012
But I...
I am being nice!

06:21.014 --> 06:23.582
Okay?
I... I-I-I talked to her.

06:23.584 --> 06:25.550
I-I asked her if there was
anything I could do to help.

06:25.552 --> 06:27.819
But I... I didn't mean it.
Nobody ever means it.

06:27.821 --> 06:29.388
Mitchell, you want
this growth in your life.

06:29.390 --> 06:31.523
That's why you asked her.
You're just scared.

06:31.525 --> 06:34.760
No, no, it was
a completely hollow offer and...

06:34.762 --> 06:35.861
Yeah, that...
That's right.

06:35.863 --> 06:37.062
Okay, george
and wendy hollowoffer.

06:37.064 --> 06:38.497
Dinner at 7:30.
Okay, bye-bye.

06:38.499 --> 06:40.265
You need this,
and I need something nice

06:40.267 --> 06:42.200
To write about you
in our christmas letter.

06:42.202 --> 06:44.035
I love you, too.
Goodbye.

06:44.037 --> 06:46.872
So... Bad news, huh?

06:46.874 --> 06:50.842
Well, only
if you hate home cooking.

06:50.844 --> 06:52.277
Oh!

06:52.279 --> 06:53.779
You're the best!
So...

06:53.781 --> 06:54.546
Mm!

06:54.548 --> 06:56.047
Mm.

06:56.049 --> 06:57.682
I think you got some
of my zoloft.

06:57.684 --> 06:59.050
That's okay.
I could use it.

07:06.427 --> 07:07.759
Bark mitzvah...
What a concept.

07:07.761 --> 07:09.194
Beagles and lox,
dog briskets.

07:09.196 --> 07:11.596
Whoever's in charge
of the wordplay, bravo.

07:11.598 --> 07:13.632
Is this for dogs
or for people?

07:13.634 --> 07:15.734
I hope it's for people.
I've had four of them.

07:15.736 --> 07:17.936
Are you having fun?
<i>Ay,</i> yes.

07:17.938 --> 07:21.306
Before today, I had never
seen a gravy fountain.

07:21.308 --> 07:24.709
Oh, gumdrop, look!
Stella's here!

07:24.711 --> 07:26.278
Everybody,
let's get a picture.

07:27.714 --> 07:30.582
Pupparazzi!
How great is that?

07:30.584 --> 07:31.817
Everybody squeeze in.

07:33.720 --> 07:35.320
Be careful of her cysts.
She'll nip you.

07:35.322 --> 07:36.555
O-okay.

07:36.557 --> 07:38.423
Okay, one more.
Doodles blinked.

07:38.425 --> 07:40.392
Now, really get tight
this time.

07:40.394 --> 07:41.793
No! No, no, no!

07:41.795 --> 07:43.929
Enough. Enough.
Oh, Gloria... Gloria.

07:43.931 --> 07:45.397
Gloria, honey,
I... listen.

07:45.399 --> 07:47.065
I-I know
you're not a dog person.

07:47.067 --> 07:48.500
No, I'm okay
with the dogs.

07:48.502 --> 07:50.669
I'm just not
a dog-person person.

07:52.105 --> 07:53.939
You said that this party
was going to be normal.

07:53.941 --> 07:55.106
It's just fun.

07:56.477 --> 07:58.243
There's a buffet
and an open bar for dogs.

07:58.245 --> 08:00.345
My cousin
got married on a raft.

08:00.347 --> 08:03.515
I tried to play along, Jay,
but... but this is crazy.

08:03.517 --> 08:04.983
I have to go home.

08:04.985 --> 08:06.485
Gloria, now,
do you think it's fair

08:06.487 --> 08:08.854
To use the word "crazy"
about a...

08:11.325 --> 08:14.259
I-I'll see you at home,
Gloria.

08:15.963 --> 08:17.996
Oh, thank you so much,
you guys.

08:17.998 --> 08:20.599
God, where were you when I was
looking for the perfect man?

08:20.601 --> 08:21.933
Well,
probably in missouri

08:21.935 --> 08:23.034
At a bar called
kansas city meats

08:23.036 --> 08:24.503
Doing the same thing.
Funny!

08:26.306 --> 08:28.173
Look at that smile.
What?

08:28.175 --> 08:30.609
That's what being nice
feels like.

08:30.611 --> 08:32.611
I like it.
I'm proud of you.

08:32.613 --> 08:33.845
Well, I'm just
letting a person

08:33.847 --> 08:35.447
I barely know
sleep in my home.

08:35.448 --> 08:36.715
I don't know if I'd use
the word "hero," but...

08:36.717 --> 08:37.982
"hero"?

08:37.985 --> 08:39.351
Stop it.
You're embarrassing me.

08:41.221 --> 08:43.355
Oh, god.
Oh!

08:43.357 --> 08:45.056
Hey,
you guys have a cat?

08:45.058 --> 08:47.058
Um, how about I freshen up
that wine, huh?

08:47.060 --> 08:49.060
Oh, no. I am good.
Okay, um...

08:49.062 --> 08:51.463
In fact, Cam, what
are... what are we doing
in the living room, here?

08:51.465 --> 08:52.531
You know?

08:52.533 --> 08:54.165
Yeah, oh,
you know what?

08:54.167 --> 08:55.967
We haven't even given brenda
a tour of our ga... uh, garage.

08:55.969 --> 08:57.402
Our... our garage.
Oh, no.
I don't like garages.

08:57.404 --> 08:59.638
That's where doug
kept his precious sailboat.

08:59.640 --> 09:00.872
No eating on the boat.

09:00.874 --> 09:02.507
No drinking on the boat.

09:02.509 --> 09:04.209
All because the one time
I went on the boat, I spilled.

09:04.211 --> 09:06.978
Well, guess what.
Boats go like this.
Oh, geez.

09:06.980 --> 09:09.347
Whoo! You know?!
And I'm like...

09:10.751 --> 09:13.752
Who... who loves a thing
more than a person?

09:13.754 --> 09:14.920
A monster.
Mm.

09:14.922 --> 09:16.855
Have we shown you
our shed?

09:16.857 --> 09:18.390
There's a shed.

09:18.392 --> 09:20.091
He knew what he was
getting into when he married me.

09:20.093 --> 09:22.093
I'm a little messy.

09:22.095 --> 09:23.828
Well, guess what, doug!

09:23.830 --> 09:26.197
Life's a little messy.

09:26.199 --> 09:29.334
Okay, my sinuses leak,
my... my ears run,

09:29.336 --> 09:31.937
And I have
hyperactive sweat glands, but...

09:31.939 --> 09:34.940
You know what?
I do need a refill.

09:34.942 --> 09:36.675
Yeah.

09:36.677 --> 09:38.777
Well, I'm not surprised.
She's losing a lot of fluids.

09:38.779 --> 09:41.446
It's as if doug was over here.
I know. I saw that.

09:42.682 --> 09:43.782
Alec!

09:43.784 --> 09:45.450
Hey.

09:45.452 --> 09:48.119
His dumb dad got transferred
to dumb africa

09:48.121 --> 09:49.955
To operate on some dumb babies.

09:49.957 --> 09:52.958
So fixing <i>their</i> hearts
is worth breaking <i>mine?</i>

09:52.960 --> 09:54.292
It's kind of worth it.

09:54.294 --> 09:55.961
He can do
like six operations a day.

09:55.963 --> 09:58.763
Yeah. I-I-I understand.
I'm sorry I'm lashing out.

09:58.765 --> 10:01.232
I-I just
really like you.

10:01.234 --> 10:02.634
I still like you.

10:02.636 --> 10:06.271
You're making this worse.
Bye, alec.

10:06.273 --> 10:08.373
Bye, Alex.

10:08.375 --> 10:09.774
Hey.

10:09.776 --> 10:11.242
I knew you couldn't leave
without one last kiss!

10:11.244 --> 10:13.812
We can work this out!

10:13.814 --> 10:16.815
I'm... I'm... I'm gonna
regret that, aren't I?

10:16.817 --> 10:19.284
Uh, I was hoping you could
throw this away for me.

10:19.286 --> 10:21.353
Yeah. Sure.

10:28.495 --> 10:31.496
So, honey,
we've been talking,

10:31.498 --> 10:33.431
And we want to meet
your boyfriend.
Mm-hmm.

10:33.433 --> 10:35.233
You just missed him.

10:35.235 --> 10:36.334
He was here?

10:36.336 --> 10:39.738
He just left.
This is his cup.

10:39.740 --> 10:41.272
Oh, look at that.

10:41.274 --> 10:44.175
Oh, it looks
like "Alex."

10:44.177 --> 10:46.778
His name is alec.
The "c" just got smudged.

10:46.780 --> 10:49.814
Honey, his name is alec.
But the "c" got smudged.

10:49.816 --> 10:51.683
Yeah, um, well,
why don't you just text him

10:51.685 --> 10:53.284
And then invite him back
for dinner?

10:53.286 --> 10:55.120
I can't.
He broke up with me.

10:55.122 --> 10:56.421
Mm.
Oh, no.

10:56.423 --> 10:58.823
He's moving to africa.

10:58.825 --> 11:01.593
Because they need
grocery models in africa.

11:01.595 --> 11:03.862
Honey, I'm so sorry.

11:03.864 --> 11:05.096
They broke up.

11:05.098 --> 11:06.765
I miss him.

11:06.767 --> 11:08.500
Oh, don't worry.

11:08.502 --> 11:11.269
Soon it will be like
he never existed.

11:12.471 --> 11:14.139
Okay.

11:14.141 --> 11:15.940
<i>Ay, dios mío,</i> Manny.
What's going on with Joe?

11:15.942 --> 11:17.308
He's a drug addict.

11:17.310 --> 11:20.045
After two hours
of mind-liquefying "zooboo,"

11:20.047 --> 11:22.781
I briefly put on a classic
movie, and he freaked out.

11:22.783 --> 11:24.182
If he could walk better,

11:24.184 --> 11:26.384
I'd seriously suggest
a 12-step program.

11:26.386 --> 11:28.620
<i>Ay,</i> no, Joe.
No more "zooboo."

11:28.622 --> 11:31.656
Thank you.
<i>Ay,</i> no.
Turn the big tv off.

11:31.658 --> 11:34.759
If he sees it on, he's going to
want to watch his show.

11:36.295 --> 11:37.729
Why are you home?

11:37.731 --> 11:40.732
Buster's party
was a bark mitzvah.

11:40.734 --> 11:43.702
I don't know why Jay
would take me to this place.

11:43.704 --> 11:44.803
I don't know.

11:44.805 --> 11:46.471
Maybe this dog stuff
is his way

11:46.473 --> 11:48.640
Of trying to find
a common interest with you.

11:48.642 --> 11:50.408
It's hard.

11:50.410 --> 11:53.378
You don't like golf or scotch
or eisenhower documentaries.

11:53.380 --> 11:55.080
It's true.
I don't like ike.

11:55.082 --> 11:58.216
But the people in this party,
they are so obsessed with dogs.

11:58.218 --> 12:01.519
Even the punch bowl
was in the shape of a toilet.

12:01.521 --> 12:03.154
Well, it's not like Jay

12:03.156 --> 12:04.823
Doesn't get out of
his comfort zone for you.

12:04.825 --> 12:06.858
He's going to your
green-card picnic tomorrow.

12:06.860 --> 12:08.326
You're right.

12:08.328 --> 12:11.930
He even bought star-spangled
sombreros for everybody.

12:11.932 --> 12:13.264
It's the wrong country.

12:13.266 --> 12:15.734
He never listens,
but... but he's sweet.

12:15.736 --> 12:17.602
You know what?

12:17.604 --> 12:19.871
I should go back
to that party.

12:19.873 --> 12:21.573
You guys want to come?

12:21.575 --> 12:23.441
Might as well.

12:23.443 --> 12:25.877
They had a pretty good spread
at buster's bris.

12:25.879 --> 12:27.912
Okay, let's get this woman
into bed

12:27.914 --> 12:30.348
And, in the morning, out of
the house as fast as we can.

12:30.350 --> 12:32.250
Honestly, I don't know
how straight guys do it.

12:32.252 --> 12:33.852
Probably without
those hand gestures.

12:34.855 --> 12:36.454
So, nice bath? Ahh.

12:36.456 --> 12:38.857
Oh, yeah, the best.
I'm so ready for bed.

12:38.859 --> 12:41.025
Okay.
Ooh, by the way,
I left a ring in there.

12:41.027 --> 12:43.128
Oh, well, we'll get at it
with some bleach in the morning.

12:43.130 --> 12:44.529
No, no, no,
my wedding ring.

12:44.531 --> 12:45.864
I just don't feel
like wearing it anymore.

12:45.866 --> 12:47.198
Oh, well,
goodbye, bad memories,

12:47.200 --> 12:49.234
Hello to our guest couch,
the cloud.

12:49.236 --> 12:50.468
Ahh!

12:50.470 --> 12:52.237
That's a small cloud.

12:52.239 --> 12:53.805
Oh, you know what?
It's deceptively comfy.

12:53.807 --> 12:55.440
I sleep on it all the time.
Oh.

12:55.442 --> 12:57.108
Yeah, if I don't
beat him to it first.
Really?

12:57.110 --> 12:58.743
Oh, okay.

12:58.745 --> 13:00.445
All right.
So, there you are.

13:00.447 --> 13:01.980
Okay.
Okay, yeah.

13:01.982 --> 13:03.481
I'm not... I'm pretty sure
this isn't gonna work.

13:03.483 --> 13:04.949
No, no, this will be fine.
This will be fine.

13:04.951 --> 13:06.284
This is what I always do.
It's not a big deal.

13:06.286 --> 13:07.752
Just make this up nice
for you.

13:07.754 --> 13:09.053
There we go. Okay.
Oh, my.

13:09.055 --> 13:10.321
See you
in the morning.

13:10.323 --> 13:11.656
Yeah, but my...
My head's...

13:11.658 --> 13:13.558
Oh.
What we were thinking?

13:13.560 --> 13:15.160
Here. Come on.
There it is right there.

13:15.162 --> 13:16.494
There you go.
Okay. Night-night.
Night-night.

13:16.496 --> 13:17.495
Hey, guys.

13:17.497 --> 13:19.097
Here's an idea.

13:19.099 --> 13:22.066
What if I just slept on
your couch in the living room?

13:22.068 --> 13:24.335
Uh...
Uh...

13:26.306 --> 13:27.639
Uh...

13:27.641 --> 13:28.673
I'm shaking.

13:28.675 --> 13:29.974
Why? Problem solved.

13:29.976 --> 13:32.110
No, she's making
the whole house shake.

