Hey, guys. You're back?
What's going on?

13:44.791 --> 13:47.025
I'm sorry. I love you,
and you love dog parties.

13:47.027 --> 13:49.527
So that means
that I love dog parties.

13:49.529 --> 13:50.929
You don't think
it's crazy anymore?

13:50.931 --> 13:52.363
I didn't say that.

13:52.365 --> 13:54.165
But Manny's right.

13:54.167 --> 13:57.702
We should get more involved
in each other's activities.

13:57.704 --> 13:59.671
Wow.
So, this was <i>your</i> idea?

13:59.673 --> 14:01.272
Well, it's sort of
the foundation

14:01.274 --> 14:03.341
Of any healthy marriage,
but I did bring it up.

14:03.343 --> 14:04.609
This is great!

14:04.611 --> 14:06.010
Well, come on.
Give me a hand.

14:06.012 --> 14:07.812
We'll grab you and your mom
an ice-cream bone.

14:07.814 --> 14:09.180
Oh.

14:09.182 --> 14:10.715
I didn't do much.
I just...

14:10.717 --> 14:12.784
Ruined my plan, that's all.
I wanted her to leave!

14:12.786 --> 14:14.118
What?

14:14.120 --> 14:15.386
She was supposed to
storm out of here.

14:15.388 --> 14:17.222
And after,
I go home and say,

14:17.224 --> 14:19.324
"maybe we should
do some things separately."

14:19.326 --> 14:21.826
I was gonna use
her bailing out of this

14:21.828 --> 14:24.562
As a chip to get out of
that stupid picnic tomorrow.

14:24.564 --> 14:25.964
But now
I've got no chip.

14:25.966 --> 14:27.866
Hey, how about next time
you devise a plan

14:27.868 --> 14:30.001
To avoid expressing a feeling,
clue me in.

14:30.003 --> 14:32.203
You can't be clued in.
You're a patsy.

14:32.205 --> 14:34.472
Hey, um, there was talk
of an ice-cream bone?

14:34.474 --> 14:37.675
I made that up, too.
Use your head!

14:39.212 --> 14:41.312
Hey, honey, you alone?

14:41.314 --> 14:43.715
Do you see anyone else
in here?

14:43.717 --> 14:45.483
Do you?

14:45.485 --> 14:49.020
Sweetheart, your father and I
think we owe you an apology.

14:49.022 --> 14:50.588
For what?
Well, this morning

14:50.590 --> 14:52.657
When we didn't think
the rose could be for you,

14:52.659 --> 14:54.559
It seemed like
maybe it hurt your feelings.

14:54.561 --> 14:56.261
I guess. A little.

14:56.263 --> 14:58.196
I am so sorry
to make you feel bad.

14:58.198 --> 15:01.366
And it is completely believable
that you would have an admirer.

15:01.368 --> 15:02.400
Okay.

15:02.402 --> 15:03.735
What we're worried
about

15:03.737 --> 15:05.737
Is that we have created
an environment

15:05.739 --> 15:08.039
In which you feel
it's necessary to...

15:08.041 --> 15:09.540
Embelli...
Fanta...

15:09.542 --> 15:10.875
Exagger...
Oh, my god.

15:10.877 --> 15:12.510
You guys don't think
alec is real?

15:12.512 --> 15:14.779
Sweetheart, I remember
the pressure there was

15:14.781 --> 15:17.015
To fit in in high school.
So do I.

15:17.017 --> 15:19.350
And whether you try to fit in
by saying you fought a baby bear

15:19.352 --> 15:21.619
Or by making up
a boyfriend...

15:21.621 --> 15:23.254
You guys
are so unbelievable.

15:23.256 --> 15:24.956
You really think
I'm that pathetic

15:24.958 --> 15:27.258
That I'd have to create
some imaginary boyfriend?

15:27.260 --> 15:30.528
You know what's not imaginary?
Your feelings.

15:30.530 --> 15:32.063
Okay, don't! Don't!

15:32.065 --> 15:34.132
F.Y.I., I changed
my facebook status to "single"

15:34.134 --> 15:35.733
About an hour ago,
and guess what.

15:35.735 --> 15:37.068
I already have a date.

15:37.070 --> 15:39.103
You don't believe me,
do you?

15:39.105 --> 15:41.105
Sweetheart, you've had
two boyfriends in 30 seconds.

15:41.107 --> 15:42.473
That practically
Haley's record.

15:42.475 --> 15:44.876
Well, he's real.
His name is teddy.

15:44.878 --> 15:47.378
His name is... Teddy?

15:47.380 --> 15:48.947
Yeah, uh-huh.

15:48.949 --> 15:50.481
Teddy keyes.

15:50.483 --> 15:52.583
Oh.

15:52.585 --> 15:54.786
And what do we know
about this young man?

15:54.788 --> 15:56.387
He's new to our school.

15:56.389 --> 16:00.224
He works at some mattress
store... mattress king.

16:00.226 --> 16:01.893
And he's a bit
of a bad boy.

16:01.895 --> 16:03.761
He had a little problem
with shoplifting.

16:03.763 --> 16:05.563
He spent some time
in juvie.

16:05.565 --> 16:08.299
But, you know, he's not really
my type. He's just a rebound.

16:08.301 --> 16:09.667
So I guess
it doesn't really matter.

16:09.669 --> 16:11.602
Ugh, why am I
even talking to you guys?

16:11.604 --> 16:12.537
Leave!

16:14.173 --> 16:15.873
Get out!

16:19.178 --> 16:20.778
Did you see the look
in her eyes?

16:20.780 --> 16:22.447
Like she believed
everything she was saying.

16:22.449 --> 16:24.415
That's terrifying.
Like this guy I knew in college.

16:24.417 --> 16:26.317
He was always telling me
about these "crazy parties"

16:26.319 --> 16:27.585
That were
"full of women."

16:27.587 --> 16:28.753
But when I'd ask him
where they were,

16:28.755 --> 16:30.088
He'd give me
a fake address.

16:30.090 --> 16:32.323
Makes me wonder
what else she's making up.

16:32.325 --> 16:34.692
I have never met that girl
she tutors in math.

16:34.694 --> 16:36.027
Esther choi?
Me neither.

16:36.029 --> 16:37.695
Because
she doesn't exist!

16:37.697 --> 16:40.365
There is not an esther choi on
earth who needs math tutoring.

16:40.367 --> 16:42.500
She needs help, Claire.
What do we do?

16:42.502 --> 16:44.102
I mean, should we send her
back to that therapist?

16:44.104 --> 16:45.436
The one
we've never met?

16:45.438 --> 16:47.271
No! Wait!

16:47.273 --> 16:49.907
Don't open it! Move away!
It's for me! Move!

16:53.112 --> 16:55.346
Damn. You look hot.

16:55.348 --> 16:57.382
The roses are from you, teddy?

16:57.384 --> 16:59.817
Yeah, I met a guy in juvie
who works at the cemetery.

16:59.819 --> 17:01.486
They got flowers
all over the place.

17:01.488 --> 17:03.654
Oh,
I also got you this.

17:03.656 --> 17:05.455
Sweet. Let's go.

17:05.458 --> 17:07.992
My other one of these cracked,
so you can use this one.

17:07.993 --> 17:09.527
Okay.

17:09.529 --> 17:12.296
Yes! Our little girl
isn't crazy!

17:12.298 --> 17:13.397
Teddy's real!

17:13.400 --> 17:15.733
Real freaky!
I'm going!

17:19.539 --> 17:21.539
Cam, you're snoring.

17:21.540 --> 17:22.707
What? Sorry.

17:24.477 --> 17:25.710
Was that me?

17:25.712 --> 17:27.912
Oh, my god.
Oh, my god.

17:27.914 --> 17:29.814
What is she doing
out here?

17:29.816 --> 17:32.183
Well, she has
that restless leg.
Both of them?

17:32.185 --> 17:34.886
Oh, my gosh,
get the ice cream!

17:34.888 --> 17:36.187
What do we do?
Should we wake her up?

17:36.189 --> 17:37.588
And say what?

17:37.590 --> 17:39.757
"Would you mind terribly
getting off our couch?

17:39.759 --> 17:41.159
You seem to
be glazing it."

17:41.161 --> 17:42.527
Do you have
a better idea?

17:42.529 --> 17:44.362
Okay, okay,
go around the back.

17:44.364 --> 17:45.730
What am I doing?
What am I doing?

17:45.732 --> 17:48.366
We'll get this
underneath her.

17:48.368 --> 17:50.868
Once, I helped a sow give birth
to nine baby piglets

17:50.870 --> 17:52.236
On our living room floor.

17:52.238 --> 17:54.238
Didn't get a drop of nothin'
on the linoleum.

17:54.240 --> 17:56.007
We're gonna get back to why
the sow was in the living room.

17:56.009 --> 17:57.241
Lady di's wedding.
It was beautiful.

17:57.243 --> 17:58.543
Cam,
she's gonna wake up.

17:58.545 --> 18:00.344
Oh, please, she's got
enough pills in her,

18:00.346 --> 18:01.879
She's gonna rattle
like a maraca.

18:01.881 --> 18:02.947
Roll!

18:02.949 --> 18:06.217
Doug, no, I don't wanna.

18:06.219 --> 18:08.186
Okay, okay, what do I do?
What do I do?

18:08.188 --> 18:09.787
You come back
around this way.

18:09.789 --> 18:11.422
No, doug.

18:11.424 --> 18:13.257
Now, what we're gonna do
is I'll push her this way

18:13.259 --> 18:14.292
And pull the blanket.

18:14.294 --> 18:16.194
Okay, I got to pull her?
Okay.

18:17.630 --> 18:19.864
I'm losing her.
I'm losing her.
Oh!

18:22.901 --> 18:25.303
This could work, too.
It's fine.

18:25.305 --> 18:26.471
Ow!

18:26.473 --> 18:27.972
Hi.

18:27.974 --> 18:29.040
Hey.

18:29.042 --> 18:30.808
What... what happened?

18:30.810 --> 18:32.477
You were having
a really bad dream,

18:32.479 --> 18:34.378
And then you rolled right off
of our uncomfortable sofa.

18:34.380 --> 18:36.647
I'm sorry.
I-I was lonely.

18:36.649 --> 18:38.249
I Came out here,

18:38.251 --> 18:40.384
And then I wound up
waking up the whole house.

18:40.386 --> 18:42.487
I'm the worst houseguest
in the world!

18:42.489 --> 18:43.821
Don't.
Don't.

18:43.823 --> 18:45.957
Doug was right.
I'm gonna die alone.

18:45.959 --> 18:47.925
Don't.
Don't.

18:47.927 --> 18:49.293
Okay, come on.

18:49.295 --> 18:51.162
Can you please
be quiet?

18:51.164 --> 18:54.065
I'm so sorry, Lily.
It's all my fault.

18:54.067 --> 18:55.633
My head hurts.

18:55.635 --> 18:57.768
I'm gonna get you
some aspirin.
Okay.

18:57.770 --> 19:01.405
Cam, are we
terrible people?

19:01.407 --> 19:03.341
For protecting
a vanderkoff?

19:03.343 --> 19:04.742
He hanged himself
last year.

19:04.744 --> 19:06.477
It's not like they're
making more of those.

19:06.479 --> 19:07.945
We just rolled
a bipolar divorcée

19:07.947 --> 19:09.080
Face-first
onto a hardwood floor.

19:09.082 --> 19:10.448
All to protect a couch.

19:10.450 --> 19:13.017
It's not just a couch.
Our one nice thing.

19:13.019 --> 19:15.953
The last seven years have been
about sticky countertops

19:15.955 --> 19:18.456
And horsy shower curtains
and childproof locks.

19:18.458 --> 19:20.024
Do you know
what's in this drawer?

19:20.026 --> 19:21.425
I don't know
what's in this drawer.
I have no idea.

19:21.427 --> 19:23.094
Look, I know it's frustrating,
all right?

19:23.096 --> 19:24.862
But is that really a reason
to choose a thing over a person?

19:24.864 --> 19:27.331
I mean, come on.
We're no better than doug.

19:28.801 --> 19:31.302
I guess it's not a great example
to set for Lily.

19:31.304 --> 19:33.671
Maybe we <i>don't</i> deserve
one nice thing.

19:34.940 --> 19:37.375
"And when the sun
Came out, all the turtles,

19:37.377 --> 19:39.677
from abner to zeke,
had fun at the picnic."

19:39.679 --> 19:41.979
Mnh.
"a rainy day for turtles."

19:41.981 --> 19:44.715
Aww. It always
makes Lily feel better.

19:44.717 --> 19:46.384
I guess
she just thought that...

19:46.386 --> 19:49.220
We do have
one nice thing.

19:49.222 --> 19:50.688
"And a beautiful rain..."

19:51.958 --> 19:53.925
Well, we don't have to
watch it die.

19:58.463 --> 20:00.198
Let's go, Jay!

20:00.200 --> 20:02.667
We're supposed to be
at the picnic in 20 minutes!

20:02.669 --> 20:04.402
They've been living in a van
for six years.

20:04.404 --> 20:06.504
They can wait
a little longer.

20:06.506 --> 20:09.040
So, today,
instead of watching the game,

20:09.042 --> 20:11.209
I'll be playing lawn darts
with colombians,

20:11.211 --> 20:13.010
Thanks to you
not using your brain.

20:13.012 --> 20:14.412
Here we go...
"the sting."

20:14.414 --> 20:16.013
Well, someone's getting
what they want today.

20:16.015 --> 20:18.249
You finally get to watch
your precious movie, huh?

20:18.251 --> 20:20.418
"A classic tale
about a long con."

20:20.420 --> 20:21.752
Well, you're welcome.

20:21.754 --> 20:23.821
Wait a minute.

20:23.823 --> 20:25.856
"Rogues and double-crossers
abound.

20:25.858 --> 20:27.525
Who will
outsmart whom?"

20:27.527 --> 20:28.726
Son of a bitch.

20:28.728 --> 20:30.595
You knew I was
using the bark mitzvah

20:30.597 --> 20:32.096
As a bargaining chip.

20:32.098 --> 20:34.365
That's why you talked Gloria
into coming back...

20:34.367 --> 20:36.867
So I couldn't weasel my way
out of this stupid picnic

20:36.869 --> 20:38.669
And you'd get
the big tv.

20:38.671 --> 20:40.571
Well,
I'm onto you now.

20:40.573 --> 20:42.707
I was just reading
off the dvd box.

20:48.113 --> 20:49.547
I mean, can you believe

20:49.549 --> 20:50.948
All the stuff brenda
brought for one night?

20:50.950 --> 20:52.883
I know. Look at all this stuff
over here.

20:52.885 --> 20:54.118
Super replenishing balm?

20:54.120 --> 20:56.120
Uh, pore-reducing
booster serum?

20:56.122 --> 20:58.889
Anti-aging
buffing beads?

20:58.891 --> 21:01.192
It must be so hard
to be a girl.

21:01.194 --> 21:02.560
I know. I know.

21:02.562 --> 21:03.694
It really makes
you worry about the world

21:03.696 --> 21:05.363
We're sending
Lily out into.

21:05.365 --> 21:06.864
Well, there's so much pressure
on girls to be perfect.

21:06.866 --> 21:07.865
You ready?
Yep.

21:09.602 --> 21:11.535
The thing is, Cam, all we can do
is instill our beliefs in her

21:11.537 --> 21:13.271
And hope that she makes
good choices.

21:13.273 --> 21:14.605
Calming mister?

21:14.607 --> 21:15.806
It does feel nice
to talk about it.

21:15.808 --> 21:17.208
No, this is
a calming mister.

21:17.210 --> 21:18.909
I just bought this.
Oh, god, yes.

